1
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:07,646
是我。
C'est moi.

2
00:03:09,481 --> 00:03:12,401
我还以为你不会出现了。
I thought you'd never show up.

3
00:03:12,484 --> 00:03:15,821
我们正赶时间。
We're crowding call time.

4
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:20,033
钢琴弹起来。这会很短。我会把它编成密码。
Get the piano going. This will be a short one. I'll put it in code.

5
00:03:51,064 --> 00:03:52,274
什么耸人听闻的吗?
Anything sensational?

6
00:03:52,357 --> 00:03:57,028
不。有些沥青铀矿。四十车。
No. Some are pitchblende. Forty carloads.

7
00:03:57,112 --> 00:04:00,323
——向北?-是的。为德国。
- Heading north? - Yeah. For Germany.

8
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:06,389
高杯酒。他甚至都没来得及签字。
Highball. He didn't even get the chance to sign off.

9
00:05:48,139 --> 00:05:53,979
从捷克斯洛伐克沥青铀矿。从西班牙沥青铀矿。
Pitchblende from czechoslovakia. Pitchblende from Spain.

10
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:57,232
在过去的30天里从德国运出了250辆车。
Two hundred and fifty carloads out of Germany in the past 30 days.

11
00:05:57,315 --> 00:06:01,319
英国情报机构表示，他们已经从挪威拿走了全部的独居石。
And British intelligence says they've taken the whole output of monazite from Norway.

12
00:06:01,403 --> 00:06:05,073
我们的问题是我们没有足够的人来分析科学数据。
Our trouble is we haven't enough people who can analyse scientific data.

13
00:06:06,658 --> 00:06:08,660
沥青铀矿和独居石。
Pitchblende and monazite.

14
00:06:10,537 --> 00:06:14,708
我明天才回来。我得找个能分析的人谈谈。
I'll be out of town till tomorrow. I've got to talk to somebody who can analyse it.

15
00:06:45,947 --> 00:06:46,948
谁在那?
Who's there?

16
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:49,492
一个兄弟会的老兄弟。
An old fraternity brother.

17
00:06:57,417 --> 00:07:01,588
克莱门! 你好吗?
Why, clem! How are you?

18
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:06,760
不知道我现在怎么样。我在地窖里转来转去破门而入就为了找到你。
Don't know how I am. I've been wandering through cellars... And breaking down doors trying to get to you.

19
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:08,762
-你有事瞒着我吗?——没有。
- Are you hiding something from me? - No.

20
00:07:08,845 --> 00:07:11,598
但你在瞒我什么?我以为你参军了。
But what are you hiding from me? I thought you were in the army.

21
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:13,975
为了让你明白，我是个上校。
To put you in your place, I'm a colonel.

22
00:07:14,059 --> 00:07:16,645
-那为什么穿便服?-我在0.8.8。
- Then why the civilian clothes? - I'm in 0.8.8.

23
00:07:16,728 --> 00:07:20,231
-没听说过。——这很好。我们不应该引起公众的注意。
- Never heard of it. - That's fine. We're not supposed to get publicity.

24
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:22,192
是战略服务办公室。
It's the office of strategic services.

25
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:25,737
在华盛顿，我们被称为秘密特工。
Around Washington we're called the cloak-and-dagger boys.

26
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:28,490
——听起来浪漫。——确定。非常。
- Sounds romantic. - Sure. Very.

27
00:07:28,573 --> 00:07:32,577
我们有很多事要做，阿尔瓦。情报工作。士气的东西。
We do a lot of things, alvah. Intelligence work. Morale stuff.

28
00:07:32,661 --> 00:07:34,579
敌后作战。
Operations behind the enemy lines.

29
00:07:34,663 --> 00:07:37,248
既然这么保密，你为什么要告诉我这些?
Why are you telling me all this if it's so hush-hush?

30
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:41,670
最近的核物理研究进展如何?
How's work in nuclear physics these days?

31
00:07:44,381 --> 00:07:47,300
——一般。-别靠近我。
- So-so. - Don't close up on me.

32
00:07:47,425 --> 00:07:50,470
这也是秘密，克莱姆，政府的工作。
Well, it's hush-hush too, clem- government work.

33
00:07:50,512 --> 00:07:53,181
我知道。你在做曼哈顿项目。
I know. You're working on the Manhattan project.

34
00:07:56,685 --> 00:07:58,311
我就是为此而来的。
That's why I'm here.

35
00:08:06,361 --> 00:08:08,863
这对你意味着什么?
What does this mean to you?

36
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:14,452
沥青铀矿铀。独居石的钍。
Pitchblende's for uranium. Monazite's for thorium.

37
00:08:16,538 --> 00:08:20,542
我们不再使用钍了。235有更方便的原子结构。
We're not working with thorium anymore. 235 has a more convenient atomic structure.

38
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:23,712
德国人有没有可能知道一些我们不知道的关于钍的事?
Any chance the Germans have learned something about thorium we don't know?

39
00:08:23,753 --> 00:08:25,005
德国人吗?
The Germans?

40
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:32,762
我可不这么认为。但这样的数量不是实验室能做的。
I wouldn't think so. But... quantities like these aren't for the laboratory.

41
00:08:32,804 --> 00:08:35,306
它们是用于大规模行动的。
They're for large-scale operations.

42
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:38,226
你觉得他们可能也在研究原子弹吗?
Do you think they might be working on an atomic bomb too?

43
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:44,274
我们都想知道。他们有头脑。
We've all wondered. They got the brains.

44
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:47,027
他们对核裂变的了解和我们一样多。
They know as much about nuclear fission as we do.

45
00:08:48,778 --> 00:08:52,699
阿尔瓦，他们在研究原子弹。
Well, alvah, they are working on an atom bomb.

46
00:08:55,702 --> 00:09:05,545
嗯哼。克莱姆，这是我第一次后悔自己是科学家。
Mm-hmm. Clem, this is the first time I was ever sorry I'm a scientist.

47
00:09:05,587 --> 00:09:07,922
为什么?
Why?

48
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:17,682
听着，再过几年，我们就能分解这个苹果的原子结构。
Look, in a few years, we'll be able to break up the atomic structure of this apple.

49
00:09:19,601 --> 00:09:24,105
当我们这样做的时候，它将成为一个炸弹。
When we do that, it will become a bomb.

50
00:09:26,691 --> 00:09:38,828
这个小苹果的能量可以摧毁这所大学，整个城市，它的医院，图书馆，它的优秀的医学院，更不用说里面所有的人了。
The energy in this one, little apple could pulverise this university, this whole town, its fine hospitals, its libraries, its wonderful medical schools, to say nothing of all the people in it.

51
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:46,377
但是…我们还是做不出一个，小苹果。
But... We still wouldn't be able to make one, little apple.

52
00:09:48,963 --> 00:09:53,301
我们有点超前了。社会还没有为原子能做好准备。
We're running ahead of ourselves. Society isn't ready for atomic energy.

53
00:09:55,512 --> 00:09:57,472
我吓坏了。
I'm scared stiff.

54
00:09:59,057 --> 00:10:03,311
这是第一次，成千上万的科学家联合在一起，共同研究什么?
For the first time, thousands of allied scientists are working together to make what?

55
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:09,067
一个炸弹!但是，战前谁愿意资助消灭肺结核的科学研究呢?
A bomb! But who was willing to finance science before the war to wipe out tuberculosis?

56
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:13,196
我们什么时候能拿到十亿美元去消灭癌症?
And when are we gonna be given a billion dollars to wipe out cancer?

57
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:15,782
我告诉你，我们可以在一年内完成。
I tell you, we could do it in one year.

58
00:10:27,252 --> 00:10:33,800
但如果有人要研制原子弹，你希望是我们，而不是纳粹。
But if anybody's going to develop the atom bomb, you want it to be us, not the Nazis.

59
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:36,052
没有多少选择。
Not much choice in that.

60
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:40,014
阿尔瓦，我们需要更多训练有素的人。
Alvah, we need more trained men on this.

61
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:42,642
我们得知道德国人走了多远。
We've got to know how far the Germans have gone.

62
00:10:42,725 --> 00:10:45,436
他们工作的地方。我们如何阻止他们。
Where they're working. How we can stop them.

63
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:47,438
我们大部分的探员都没有装备。
Most of our agents aren't equipped.

64
00:10:47,522 --> 00:10:49,440
他们不知道要找什么。
They don't know what to look for.

65
00:10:49,524 --> 00:10:53,987
他们遗漏了一些线索，我知道。这是一场比赛。
They're missing clues, I know. This is a race.

66
00:10:54,028 --> 00:10:56,489
不是德国人就是我们。
It's the Germans or us.

67
00:10:56,573 --> 00:11:00,410
我们得让更多的科学家加入我们的队伍。
We've got to get more scientists into our outfit.

68
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:02,495
那我在这里做什么呢?
How about what I'm doing here?

69
00:11:02,579 --> 00:11:06,416
我已经被授权让你离开了。你知道问题所在。
I'm already authorised to take you off. You know the problem.

70
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:10,128
你是单身。你会说一点德语。但你必须成为志愿者。
You're single. You can speak a little German. But you've got to volunteer.

71
00:11:12,672 --> 00:11:17,677
曾经有一段时间，我想成为某种秘密特工。
There was a time when I thought I'd like to become some sort of a secret agent.

72
00:11:17,719 --> 00:11:20,054
我八岁的时候就放弃了。
I gave it up at the age of eight.

73
00:11:23,224 --> 00:11:26,728
好吧，兄弟，你现在是间谍了。
Okay, brother, you're now a spy.

74
00:11:29,189 --> 00:11:31,941
我有两张回华盛顿的机票。
I've got two plane tickets back to Washington.

75
00:11:31,983 --> 00:11:34,402
我能有时间结束这一切吗?
Can I even have time to wind things up here?

76
00:11:34,485 --> 00:11:38,448
通常我们会给你几周的时间，但我想让你看看这个。
Ordinarily we'd give you a few weeks, but I want you to take a look at this.

77
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:45,914
认识她吗?
Know her?

78
00:11:45,997 --> 00:11:49,667
卡特琳·洛多医生，最伟大的医生之一。
Dr. Katerin lodor, one of the great ones.

79
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:54,714
在匈牙利被卖给纳粹之前我是我的科学模特。
Used to be my scientific pinup girl before Hungary sold out to the Nazis.

80
00:11:54,797 --> 00:11:58,718
我猜她现在正处于德国原子研究的中心。
I suppose now she's right in the centre of German atomic work.

81
00:11:58,801 --> 00:12:01,638
-她在瑞士。从什么时候开始?
- She's in Switzerland. - Since when?

82
00:12:01,721 --> 00:12:06,226
大约六个星期。她一个人翻越了阿尔卑斯山。
About six weeks. She came over the alps... alone.

83
00:12:06,309 --> 00:12:09,312
她因肺炎住进了苏黎世的一家医院。
She's been in a hospital in Zurich with pneumonia.

84
00:12:09,354 --> 00:12:12,023
几天前她和美国领事馆取得了联系。
A few days ago she got in touch with the American consulate.

85
00:12:12,106 --> 00:12:14,609
她说要见我们的一位科学家。
Said she wanted to see one of our scientists.

86
00:12:18,738 --> 00:12:21,074
你不知道这让我有多开心。
You don't know how happy that makes me feel.

87
00:12:24,202 --> 00:12:29,123
如果她刚离开德国，她会知道这是一个极好的机会!
If she's just out of Germany she can tell... this is a terrific break!

88
00:12:29,207 --> 00:12:35,880
如果你不再为此感到高兴，回家收拾行李，过几天你就能见到她了。——好的。
If you'd stop feeling so happy about it and go home and pack a bag, - you can see her in a couple of days. - Okay.

89
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:48,661
我希望您对您的房间满意。
I hope you find your room satisfactory.

90
00:13:49,579 --> 00:13:52,248
谢谢schoen表示。
Danke schoen.

91
00:14:21,736 --> 00:14:24,238
-非常抱歉，先生-很好
- Very sorry, sir. - Quite all right.

92
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:47,178
-给你。,非常感谢。
- Here you go. - Danke sehr.

93
00:15:20,670 --> 00:15:23,548
不要回头。
Don't turn around.

94
00:15:27,802 --> 00:15:31,472
你要见的女士在安吉洛医院。
The lady you want to see is at the Angelo hospital.

95
00:15:31,514 --> 00:15:37,353
房间1-6-8。她的名字叫希柯蒂太太。
Room 1-6-8. She's there under the name of Mrs. Hickerty.

96
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:56,664
你可以进来了。
You may come in.

97
00:16:05,381 --> 00:16:07,884
请不要太久，威尔逊先生。
Not too long, please, Mr. Wilson.

98
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:19,729
你的真名是什么，威尔逊先生?
What is your real name, Mr. Wilson?

99
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:28,070
——阿尔瓦Jesper。-我知道你的工作。
- Alvah Jesper. - I know your work.

100
00:16:28,112 --> 00:16:31,407
感谢上帝你来了。你不知道我有多感激你。
Thank god you've come. You don't know how indebted I am to you.

101
00:16:31,491 --> 00:16:34,994
对我?
To me?

102
00:16:35,077 --> 00:16:41,792
当人们发现你所做的一切，他们会知道你不仅是一位伟大的物理学家，还是一位伟大的女性。
When people find out what you've done, they'll know you're not only a great physicist, but a great woman.

103
00:16:41,876 --> 00:16:45,713
也许吧。故事还没有结束。
Maybe. The story isn't ended yet.

104
00:16:47,632 --> 00:16:56,349
人们会怎么想?你会怎么想……-如果我回德国?——回去?
What will people think? What will you think... - If I were to go back to Germany? - Go back?

105
00:16:56,432 --> 00:17:01,020
但这不是你翻越阿尔卑斯山或者联系我们的原因。
Oh, but that isn't why you crossed the alps or got in touch with us.

106
00:17:01,062 --> 00:17:06,067
不。但你看，我以为我在这里很安全。
No. But you see, I thought I'd be safe here.

107
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:09,820
我不是。德国人找到我了。
I'm not. The Germans have found me here.

108
00:17:09,862 --> 00:17:12,657
昨天我收到一封盖着苏黎世邮戳的信。
Yesterday I got a letter postmarked Zurich.

109
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:16,077
我要去意大利工作。
I'm to go to Italy to work.

110
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:18,162
我一直在那里和波尔达合作。
I've been collaborating there with polda.

111
00:17:18,246 --> 00:17:22,375
——Giovanni polda ?——是的。
- Giovanni polda? - Yes.

112
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:33,261
如果我不回去，从周日开始，每天都有十个匈牙利反纳粹分子被带出集中营并被枪毙。
If I don't return, beginning Sunday, ten anti-Nazi Hungarians are to be taken out of concentration camps... And shot each day.

113
00:17:35,346 --> 00:17:40,434
每天，他们都会给我一封写有名字的信。
Each day, they promise me a letter with names.

114
00:17:44,272 --> 00:17:48,526
带着死者的照片。
With photographs of the dead people.

115
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:55,700
所以德国人在研究原子武器?
So the Germans are working on atomic weapons?

116
00:17:55,783 --> 00:17:59,328
意大利人。他们正在协调。
Italians too. They are coordinated.

117
00:17:59,412 --> 00:18:03,541
如果你回去，你的工作帮助他们成功，会发生什么?
Then what would happen if you went back and your work helped them to succeed?

118
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:06,043
如果我留在这里会怎么样?
What happens if I stay here?

119
00:18:07,878 --> 00:18:13,593
我不能眼睁睁地看着无辜的人因为我而被枪杀。
I can't live knowing that innocent people are being shot because of me.

120
00:18:17,263 --> 00:18:20,182
我将回去。
I'll go back.

121
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:25,313
我将毒药。我无法做出其他决定。
I'll take poison. I can't decide any other way.

122
00:18:34,697 --> 00:18:39,410
不如你回去和波尔达医生一起工作吧?
Suppose you went back to work with Dr. Polda?

123
00:18:39,535 --> 00:18:44,373
但是你在工作中遇到过困难吗?障碍。
But you met difficulties in your work? Obstacles.

124
00:18:44,457 --> 00:18:48,461
——明白了吗?——是的。
- Understand? - Yes.

125
00:18:48,544 --> 00:18:52,882
这是可能的。这是可能的。
That's possible. That's possible.

126
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:57,553
如果你觉得自己足够强大，你也可以帮助我们，提供一些信息。
And if you felt strong enough for it, you could help us, too, with information.

127
00:18:57,637 --> 00:19:02,642
-有沟通的方式吗?-我想是的。
- There are ways of communicating? - I think so.

128
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:12,443
我得和你讨论一下。必须做出安排，相信我，我有足够的力量去做这件事。
I'll have to discuss it. Arrangements will have to be made, and- believe me, I would be strong enough for that.

129
00:19:12,526 --> 00:19:16,197
但你得快点。他们只给了我周日的期限。
But you have to hurry. They've given me only until Sunday.

130
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:18,783
在我回去之前，我们得谈谈。
Before I go back, we have to talk.

131
00:19:20,117 --> 00:19:23,537
我需要你提供的所有信息。
I'll need every bit of information you have.

132
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:31,462
如果你知道当英国人轰炸挪威的重水工厂时，他们是如何击退他们的，这对他们来说意味着几个月的延迟。
If you only knew how the British set them back... When they bombed that heavy water plant in Norway it meant a delay of months for them.

133
00:19:33,214 --> 00:19:35,591
但如果你不能安排呢?
But what if you can't arrange this?

134
00:19:35,675 --> 00:19:40,221
-可以安排。——我将
- It can be arranged. - I will

135
00:19:44,517 --> 00:19:49,313
噢,我忘了。他们一直在担心我的肺。我该照x光了。
Oh, I forgot. They keep worrying over my lungs. I'm due for an X-ray.

136
00:19:49,397 --> 00:19:52,733
-我很乐意等。-明天早上再来。
- I'll be glad to wait. - Come back tomorrow morning.

137
00:19:52,817 --> 00:19:56,821
那我就更有力气了。我们可以聊一整天。
I'll have more strength then. We can talk all day.

138
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:58,948
什么都不用担心。
Don't worry about anything.

139
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:04,662
今晚我将睡觉。
Tonight I'll sleep.

140
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:07,748
知道你能入睡的感觉真好。
Such a good feeling to know you can sleep.

141
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:14,714
-有我的电话吗?——不,先生。
- Are there any calls for me? - No, sir.

142
00:20:14,755 --> 00:20:17,299
我在等一个电话。请在吧台那边叫我好吗?
I'm expecting a call. Will you please have me paged at the bar?

143
00:20:17,341 --> 00:20:18,592
很高兴,先生。
Glad to, sir.

144
00:20:20,261 --> 00:20:25,057
